itly requires live infra. Rejected Agentic/Workflow because no AI/ML judgment or multi-agent sequencing is involved.","test_description":"Execute `/kaizen-wip` end-to-end in a real repo context with real PR backend state in two scenarios: branch fully merged/clean and branch ahead with no PR. Assert rendered output classification text matches expected states. This catches real command wiring and infrastructure interaction failures that in-process stubs can hide.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.88,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"Branches with open or merged PRs are not flagged as stale-no-PR false positives.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Seam-map: module/interface seam (PR-state interpretation + staleness classifier). MOCK-MISS: real failure is incorrect handling of PR lifecycle states as they cross module boundaries. REAL-INFRA: behavior text does not require live API; deterministic state fixtures can expose logic defects. INTEGRATION-BRAKE: (a) no explicit live OS/network requirement in this behavior text; (b) no AI/ML dependence; (c) no multi-step agentic chain. REJECTION-GATE: rejected System because unlike behavior 4, this behavior does not require 'live repo and PR state'.","test_description":"Wire classifier with PR-state adapter contract fixtures for `open`, `merged`, `closed-unmerged`, and assert only the no-PR eligible case can become `stale-no-pr`. Include regression cases where merged PR metadata arrives with delayed sync fields. This catches interface/contract bugs causing false positives.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.12,"Integration":0.64,"System":0.22,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"Staleness detection remains correct across rebases or squash merges where commit hashes change but branch state should no longer be classified as unPRed